File: President Cyril Ramaphosa. JOHANNESBURG - President Cyril Ramaphosa and his team are expected to announce billions of rand worth of investments. This is to mitigate the devastating impact of the COVID-19 pandemic on jobs and the economy. READ: SARB warns of consequences of quantitative easing Details will be revealed at a symposium in Pretoria. It’s a culmination of months of behind-the-scenes discussions between private investors, financial institutions and government.